      </figure>
    <p>GDPR provides several rights to the data subject, whose applicability depends on the context and nature of processing taking place. DPV lists these rights at an abstract level as concepts along with their origin in specific clauses of the GDPR.</p>
    <p>In addition to DPV's concepts regarding exercise of rights, EU-GDPR provides additional concepts specific to the implementation of its rights. For example, [=SARNotice=] refers to the information provided in fulfilment of [=A15=] Right of Access, or using [=dcat:Resource=] to represent the dataset provided in fulfilment of [=A20=] Right to Data Portability.</p>
    <aside class="note" title="Forthcoming guidance on implementation of rights">
      <p>The [[[GUIDE-Rights]]] is a work-in-progress document that will provide guidance and examples for use of DPV concepts to discover, exercise, and respond to rights, including those defined by GDPR.</p>
    </aside>
    {{ list_hierarchy(modules['rights']['classes']) }}
